= The~project roadmap =

This~page contains the~list of~tasks 
considered as~a~roadmap for~Luwrain 
as it~was accepted on~November 18th, 2014.
They are the~most important 
things for~a~robust  Luwrain developing.

# {Stabilizing and cleaning the~code of~the~core.}
The~core still has a~lot of~consequents of~early time of~development.
Existence of~the~depricated  classes and methods  
makes the~work difficult.
Besides that, some classes should be~renamed 
(e.~g., 
"{{Action}}" to "{{Command}}" and
"{{AppWrapper}}" to "{{Shortcut}}"). 

# {Rethinking the~registry implementation}
The~registry at~its current state, evidently, is~very inconvenient 
and becomes a~serious barrier on~the~deployment attempts. 
It is necessary to work~out something  more felicitous.

# {Specification of~an~application template.}
The~structure of~the~typical application and its life cycle should be obvious.
The~current core state has everything needed to~get that  but 
it~is~necessary to~write additional materials as~an~introduction to~the~application creation.

#  {Platform-dependent  components for~the~proper portability support.}
It~is~necessary to~prepare reliable platform-dependent things 
which allow running on~MacOS-X or Microsoft Windows,
including installation tools.
It~is needed to~simplify a~deployment on~user machines.

# {Internationalization infrastructure.}
it~is necessary to~get unified and flexible approach to~foreign languages and national~standards  support.
That could help to~introduce Luwrain to~the~foreign communities.

# {The documentation.}
There~is a~lack of~good documentation but we should have it a~lot!

